The Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria (FAAN) has notified airlines of the withdrawal of services to Osubi Airport, Warri, Gombe Airport and Murtala Muhammed Airport Terminal Two (MMA2), it was learnt Saturday night. In a Notice To Airmen (NOTAM) issued on Saturday, December 8, 2018, FAAN stated that it will be withdrawing Aviation Security, fire fighting and rescue operations from Osubi, Gombe and MMA2 from midnight of Sunday, December 9, 2018. FAAN had earlier threatened to withdraw services to the airport owned by state government and private operators. While Gombe is managed by the state government, MMA2 and Osubi are managed by private operators. The authority gave the affected airports 30-day notice which lapsed penultimate week. FAAN to sanction agencies, operators over debt FG, MMA2 and airports concession FAAN shuts down Benin airport